quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  21,11,"How many a city that was evildoing We have shattered, and set up after it another people"
  21,12,"Then, when they perceived Our might, behold, they ran headlong out of it"
  21,13,"Run not! Return you unto the luxury that you exulted in, and your dwelling-places; haply you shall be questioned"
  21,14,"They said, 'Alas for us! We have been evildoers"
  21,15,"So they ceased not to cry, until We made them stubble, silent and still"
  21,16,"We created not the heaven and the earth, and whatsoever between them is, as playing"
  21,17,"had We desired to take to Us a diversion We would have taken it to Us from Ourselves, had We done aught"
  21,18,"Nay, but We hurl the truth against falsehood and it prevails over it, and behold, falsehood vanishes away. Then woe to you for that you describe"
  21,19,To Him belongs whosoever is in the heavens and the earth; and those who are with Him wax not too proud to do Him service neither grow weary
  21,20,glorifying Him by night and in the daytime and never failing
  21,21,Or have they taken gods out of the earth who raise the dead
  21,22,"Why, were there gods in earth and heaven other than God, they would surely go to ruin; so glory be to God, the Lord of the Throne, above that they describe"
  21,23,"He shall not be questioned as to what He does, but they shall he questioned"
  21,24,"Or have they taken gods apart from Him? Say: 'Bring your proof! This is the Remembrance of him who is with me, and the Remembrance of those before me. Nay, but the most part of them know not the truth, so therefore they are turning away"